1
00:00:02,333 --> 00:00:03,250
Tsubaki: Huh?!
How'd they get all broken?

2
00:00:03,333 --> 00:00:05,916
I hid them
and everything.

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:08,958
Maybe they dried out
too much?

4
00:00:09,041 --> 00:00:11,125
[ Whimpering ]

5
00:00:13,250 --> 00:00:16,375
[ Crying ] I worked hard
to make them,

6
00:00:16,458 --> 00:00:18,500
and now they're just dirt!
Don't cry, Tsubaki.

7
00:00:18,583 --> 00:00:21,000
It's not the end of the world.
Shut up, Kousei!

8
00:00:21,083 --> 00:00:22,500
Get out of here,
you big dummy!

9
00:00:22,583 --> 00:00:23,875
Huh?
I don't care

10
00:00:23,958 --> 00:00:26,750
if you leave me or not,
so just go away!

11
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:27,875
[ Crying ]

12
00:00:27,958 --> 00:00:29,875
[ Sighs ]

13
00:00:29,958 --> 00:00:36,541
♪♪

14
00:00:36,625 --> 00:00:38,625
[ "Nanairo Symphony" playing ]

15
00:00:38,708 --> 00:00:42,166
♪♪

16
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:45,208
[ Singing in Japanese ]

17
00:00:45,291 --> 00:00:54,250
♪♪

18
00:00:54,333 --> 00:01:03,375
♪♪

19
00:01:03,458 --> 00:01:12,416
♪♪

20
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:21,541
♪♪

21
00:01:21,625 --> 00:01:30,583
♪♪

22
00:01:30,666 --> 00:01:39,750
♪♪

23
00:01:39,833 --> 00:01:48,750
♪♪

24
00:01:48,833 --> 00:01:56,916
♪♪

25
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:06,916
♪♪

26
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,125
-Morning.
-Oh, morning.

27
00:02:08,208 --> 00:02:10,375
Young Woman: [ Laughs ]
Check out that tan.

28
00:02:14,708 --> 00:02:18,041
Young Man: I lost my whole
summer to cram school.

29
00:02:18,125 --> 00:02:20,708
-So you ready?
-Readyish.

30
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,916
[ Indistinct conversations ]

31
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,250
Kousei: I'd like to test

32
00:02:27,333 --> 00:02:28,666
for Okutsu College's
high school prep track.

33
00:02:28,750 --> 00:02:31,916
Teacher: That's in
another prefecture, right?

34
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:34,583
Yes, but my dad says
he's okay with it.

35
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:36,833
My moving, that is.

36
00:02:38,791 --> 00:02:40,791
The best conservatories
are picky.

37
00:02:40,875 --> 00:02:42,625
It all comes down
to your competition record

38
00:02:42,708 --> 00:02:46,125
and who you've trained with,
so it might not pan out.

39
00:02:46,208 --> 00:02:47,125
[ Gasps ]

40
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:49,250
That said, my mentor

41
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:50,708
thinks going overseas
might be a good fit.

42
00:02:50,791 --> 00:02:54,208
I guess there's a friend she
wants me to meet from the time

43
00:02:54,291 --> 00:02:55,208
she spent abroad.
[ Growling ]

44
00:02:55,291 --> 00:02:57,791
Thinking of the big picture.
That's good.

45
00:02:57,875 --> 00:02:59,708
<i>Stupid friend-napping Hiroko!</i>

46
00:02:59,791 --> 00:03:01,416
Best of luck.
Thank you.

47
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:02,625
[ Gasps ]

48
00:03:02,708 --> 00:03:08,166
♪♪

49
00:03:08,250 --> 00:03:10,083
<i>Go ahead. Move away.</i>

50
00:03:10,166 --> 00:03:12,250
<i>Go to the Moon,</i>
<i>for all I care.</i>

51
00:03:12,333 --> 00:03:14,583
<i>You dummy. I don't care</i>
<i>if you're with me or not,</i>

52
00:03:14,666 --> 00:03:16,500
<i>so just go away!</i>

53
00:03:16,583 --> 00:03:18,958
If you don't care
if I'm with you or not...

54
00:03:19,041 --> 00:03:20,041
[ Gasps ]

55
00:03:20,125 --> 00:03:23,000
[ Stammering ]

56
00:03:23,083 --> 00:03:24,250
[ Groans ]

57
00:03:27,416 --> 00:03:29,875
[ Groaning ]

58
00:03:29,958 --> 00:03:32,000
If you're trying
to keep it bottled up,

59
00:03:32,083 --> 00:03:33,333
it's not working out.

60
00:03:33,416 --> 00:03:34,541
We're not even counting
this one, right?

61
00:03:34,625 --> 00:03:36,333
I can read you
like a book.

62
00:03:36,416 --> 00:03:37,666
We could have had
a new school record here.

63
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:41,541
Hmm?
Hmm?

64
00:03:41,625 --> 00:03:43,333
[ Sputtering ]
Hope you had a good trip!

65
00:03:43,416 --> 00:03:44,833
Even I'm not
that clumsy.

66
00:03:44,916 --> 00:03:47,166
Well, been nice
knowing you two.

67
00:03:47,250 --> 00:03:48,291
<i>Target acquired.</i>

68
00:03:48,375 --> 00:03:49,541
[ Boys wail ]

69
00:03:49,625 --> 00:03:51,208
Watari:
I'm too cute to die!

70
00:03:51,291 --> 00:03:53,250
[ Indistinct conversations ]

71
00:03:56,541 --> 00:03:58,875
I think
I peed a little.

72
00:04:01,291 --> 00:04:03,708
Hmm.
Is it me,

73
00:04:03,791 --> 00:04:05,250
or has she been
acting kind of weird?

74
00:04:05,333 --> 00:04:08,750
<i>Oh, it's you, alright.</i>

75
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:10,916
I would just leave her alone
for a bit.

76
00:04:11,041 --> 00:04:13,833
<i>Well, excuse me</i>
<i>for falling on my face.</i>

77
00:04:13,916 --> 00:04:15,208
<i>It hurts, you know.</i>

78
00:04:15,291 --> 00:04:18,791
<i>Laughing like you haven't</i>
<i>got a care in the world.</i>

79
00:04:18,875 --> 00:04:21,125
<i>Would a compliment</i>
<i>kill you?</i>

80
00:04:21,208 --> 00:04:23,625
<i>I'd have to move.</i>

81
00:04:23,708 --> 00:04:26,500
<i>Whenever I talk to you,</i>
<i>I feel better,</i>

82
00:04:26,583 --> 00:04:28,250
<i>or I feel worse.</i>

83
00:04:28,333 --> 00:04:31,416
<i>I'm such a mess right now.</i>

84
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,083
<i>Pretty lame, huh?</i>

85
00:04:33,166 --> 00:04:34,208
[ Grunts ]

86
00:04:34,291 --> 00:04:35,541
[ Kids gasp ]

87
00:04:37,166 --> 00:04:37,750
[ Yelling ]
[ Yelling ]

88
00:04:37,833 --> 00:04:39,333
Kids:
That's crazy!

89
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,750
<i>Tsubaki.</i>

90
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:46,416
<i>They just look that way</i>
<i>'cause you're Bigfoot!</i>

91
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,583
<i>You think if you say it</i>
<i>enough times,</i>

92
00:04:48,666 --> 00:04:51,375
<i>you'll convince everyone,</i>
<i>including yourself.</i>

93
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:54,125
<i>You're too chicken</i>
<i>to face the facts.</i>

94
00:04:54,208 --> 00:05:02,166
♪♪

95
00:05:02,250 --> 00:05:05,083
[ Kids laughing ]

96
00:05:05,541 --> 00:05:15,166
♪♪

97
00:05:15,250 --> 00:05:25,166
♪♪

98
00:05:25,250 --> 00:05:35,166
♪♪

99
00:05:35,250 --> 00:05:37,166
Uh...

100
00:05:37,916 --> 00:05:40,333
Saito, I--
So, hey,

101
00:05:40,416 --> 00:05:42,000
there's this one girl
at school.

102
00:05:42,083 --> 00:05:43,333
Huh?

103
00:05:49,083 --> 00:05:50,458
An upperclassman.

104
00:05:50,541 --> 00:05:53,041
Met her, 'cause she's manager
of the baseball team.

105
00:05:53,125 --> 00:05:56,041
She's got long hair,
and she's really down to
earth,

106
00:05:56,125 --> 00:05:59,125
kind of girly, eats her chips
with chopsticks.

107
00:06:02,916 --> 00:06:05,333
It's just we're
way too much alike.

108
00:06:05,416 --> 00:06:06,916
You know what
I'm talking about.

109
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,083
Think about it.
We're both infielders,

110
00:06:09,166 --> 00:06:12,958
and we've got short hair,
and we're both kind of blunt.

111
00:06:13,041 --> 00:06:21,375
♪♪

112
00:06:21,458 --> 00:06:22,916
And when you're with me,

113
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:25,250
you always seem like you
want to be somewhere else.

114
00:06:26,666 --> 00:06:29,500
You laugh, but it's
like the nervous kind.

115
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:33,291
Me and you...

116
00:06:33,375 --> 00:06:35,875
we should be
with those quiet types, right?

117
00:06:35,958 --> 00:06:37,833
Huh? Saito.

118
00:06:37,916 --> 00:06:38,875
I didn't...

119
00:06:41,083 --> 00:06:44,666
It's not like the end
of the world or anything.

120
00:06:46,291 --> 00:06:47,000
We just didn't work out.

121
00:06:51,125 --> 00:06:52,625
I'm really sorry.

122
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:57,000
I'm sorry, Saito.

123
00:06:57,083 --> 00:06:59,208
[ Crying ]
I'm sorry.

124
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:04,250
[ Grunts ]

125
00:07:04,333 --> 00:07:06,083
Hey,
what's the big idea

126
00:07:06,166 --> 00:07:07,875
telling me sorry
over and over?

127
00:07:07,958 --> 00:07:09,833
I'm the one
who's breaking up with you.

128
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:16,000
Really, though,
thank you

129
00:07:16,083 --> 00:07:17,625
for being my girlfriend
and all.

130
00:07:21,208 --> 00:07:24,416
[ Slowly playing
"Clair de lune" ]

131
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:36,916
♪♪

132
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:37,875
Hey.

133
00:07:37,958 --> 00:07:39,583
Scoot over a bit.

134
00:07:39,666 --> 00:07:40,833
I've got to practice,
you know.

135
00:07:40,916 --> 00:07:44,125
I'm scooting!
Just hold your horses.

136
00:07:44,208 --> 00:07:47,125
I thought I heard the piano
making some weird sounds.

137
00:07:47,208 --> 00:07:47,750
Mystery solved.

138
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:49,958
'Scuse me, Mozart.

139
00:07:50,041 --> 00:07:51,083
[ Chuckles ]

140
00:07:51,166 --> 00:07:54,083
[ Playing "Clair de lune" ]

141
00:07:54,166 --> 00:08:01,541
♪♪

142
00:08:01,625 --> 00:08:08,166
♪♪

143
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:16,666
♪♪

144
00:08:16,750 --> 00:08:24,333
♪♪

145
00:08:24,416 --> 00:08:26,708
Are you gonna
ask me about it?

146
00:08:26,791 --> 00:08:28,833
No,
but I'm listening.

147
00:08:28,916 --> 00:08:34,333
♪♪

148
00:08:34,416 --> 00:08:36,541
I just got dumped.

149
00:08:38,291 --> 00:08:41,291
This older boy
that I had a crush on,

150
00:08:41,375 --> 00:08:43,791
really cute
and a good guy.

151
00:08:43,875 --> 00:08:45,500
I guess
he was kind of like

152
00:08:45,583 --> 00:08:47,125
a package
of that fancy ice cream,

153
00:08:47,208 --> 00:08:51,500
the kind you never buy,
because it's too expensive...

154
00:08:52,583 --> 00:08:54,583
the kind
people go crazy about.

155
00:08:55,583 --> 00:08:57,375
<i>The kind that's</i>
<i>not my style.</i>

156
00:08:58,833 --> 00:09:00,000
Said he liked me.

157
00:09:00,083 --> 00:09:02,333
I was thrilled,
so I went for it.

158
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,208
And now it's over.

159
00:09:09,291 --> 00:09:10,458
The worst part is...

160
00:09:16,375 --> 00:09:17,750
[ Crying ]

161
00:09:17,833 --> 00:09:19,458
I really hurt him.

162
00:09:20,083 --> 00:09:22,625
I'm such an idiot.

163
00:09:22,708 --> 00:09:25,041
How come I didn't know
what was in my heart?

164
00:09:27,375 --> 00:09:28,791
<i>I wish</i>
<i>I still didn't know.</i>

165
00:09:28,875 --> 00:09:32,958
<i>I'd give anything for life</i>
<i>to go on the way it always has.</i>

166
00:09:34,791 --> 00:09:35,916
<i>But...</i>

167
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:38,416
Well, that was
my chance at stardom.

168
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:41,125
I'd like to test
for Okutsu College's

169
00:09:41,208 --> 00:09:42,333
high school prep track.

170
00:09:44,416 --> 00:09:46,416
Tsubaki:<i> Time is moving forward</i>

171
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:47,750
<i>for Watari...</i>

172
00:09:47,833 --> 00:09:49,416
<i>and Kousei.</i>

173
00:09:49,500 --> 00:09:51,208
<i>Even when they</i>
<i>can't see what's coming,</i>

174
00:09:51,291 --> 00:09:55,375
<i>even when they're afraid,</i>
<i>they still go on...</i>

175
00:09:56,583 --> 00:09:58,833
<i>one foot in front of the other,</i>

176
00:09:58,916 --> 00:10:01,041
<i>they find the courage</i>
<i>to keep moving,</i>

177
00:10:01,125 --> 00:10:02,416
<i>supporting each other,</i>

178
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:04,458
<i>inspiring each other,</i>

179
00:10:04,541 --> 00:10:05,083
<i>working as a team.</i>

180
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,750
<i>They're on their way,</i>

181
00:10:08,833 --> 00:10:10,125
<i>and I'm stuck.</i>

182
00:10:10,208 --> 00:10:12,000
<i>I was right</i>
<i>about time stopping...</i>

183
00:10:14,166 --> 00:10:18,708
<i>but the only one</i>
<i>who got frozen was me.</i>

184
00:10:23,666 --> 00:10:25,000
[ Crying ]

185
00:10:25,083 --> 00:10:26,916
Are you gonna play
that stupid song all night,

186
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:27,958
or are you gonna
comfort me, already?!

187
00:10:28,041 --> 00:10:30,458
"Clair de lune" can wait,
you big jerk!

188
00:10:30,541 --> 00:10:32,291
I'm hurting here!

189
00:10:32,375 --> 00:10:36,750
I don't care if you're
with me or not, so go!

190
00:10:38,208 --> 00:10:39,250
[ Sniffles ]

191
00:10:39,708 --> 00:10:41,041
Alright.

192
00:10:43,208 --> 00:10:45,875
If you don't care
if I'm with you or not...

193
00:10:46,791 --> 00:10:48,875
Then I'll just stay.

194
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:52,625
You're stuck with me.

195
00:10:54,416 --> 00:10:56,291
[ Gasps ]

196
00:10:56,375 --> 00:10:57,750
What the hell's
wrong with you!

197
00:10:57,833 --> 00:10:59,166
Quit it!
You can't be super nice

198
00:10:59,250 --> 00:11:01,125
to a girl
right after she gets dumped!

199
00:11:02,250 --> 00:11:04,125
[ Playing "Clair de lune" ]

200
00:11:04,208 --> 00:11:07,125
♪♪

201
00:11:07,208 --> 00:11:09,708
It's not like I was being
extra nice to you,

202
00:11:09,791 --> 00:11:12,500
just boring old me.

203
00:11:12,583 --> 00:11:15,166
<i>Right by my side</i>

204
00:11:15,250 --> 00:11:18,583
<i>whenever I was hurting,</i>
<i>anytime I was sad,</i>

205
00:11:18,666 --> 00:11:21,583
<i>like a brother to me, but not.</i>

206
00:11:21,666 --> 00:11:22,875
Young Kousei:
You're stuck with me.

207
00:11:22,958 --> 00:11:24,416
<i>Liar.</i>

208
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:27,708
<i>Even now,</i>
<i>you're getting ready to leave.</i>

209
00:11:27,791 --> 00:11:29,625
<i>Maybe it's too late, but...</i>

210
00:11:29,708 --> 00:11:32,250
<i>I'm not giving up.</i>

211
00:11:32,333 --> 00:11:35,375
<i>I'm just a jock</i>
<i>and one of the guys,</i>

212
00:11:35,458 --> 00:11:39,291
<i>and I don't know anything</i>
<i>about the piano,</i>

213
00:11:39,375 --> 00:11:41,791
<i>but I finally know what I want.</i>

214
00:11:43,625 --> 00:11:45,625
<i>Honestly, I hate music.</i>

215
00:11:45,708 --> 00:11:48,291
<i>It's always taking</i>
<i>Kousei away from me.</i>

216
00:11:48,375 --> 00:11:50,875
[ Chuckles ]
Would you look at that?

217
00:11:50,958 --> 00:11:52,375
The moon is out.

218
00:11:52,458 --> 00:11:53,708
[ Crying ]

219
00:11:53,791 --> 00:11:56,041
Yeah. So what?

220
00:11:56,125 --> 00:11:57,708
Is that supposed
to make me feel better?

221
00:11:57,791 --> 00:11:59,375
It's pretty.

222
00:11:59,458 --> 00:12:00,583
Maybe so.

223
00:12:00,666 --> 00:12:03,041
<i>Dummy. Don't be so nice.</i>

224
00:12:03,125 --> 00:12:05,750
<i>It just makes it hurt worse.</i>

225
00:12:05,833 --> 00:12:07,833
♪♪

226
00:12:07,916 --> 00:12:10,375
<i>There's the mark.</i>

227
00:12:10,458 --> 00:12:11,708
<i>It's now or never.</i>

228
00:12:11,791 --> 00:12:14,375
<i>Time for this ice...</i>

229
00:12:16,458 --> 00:12:17,583
<i>to thaw.</i>

230
00:12:18,666 --> 00:12:21,583
[ Piano playing ]

231
00:12:21,666 --> 00:12:28,083
♪♪

232
00:12:28,166 --> 00:12:34,416
♪♪

233
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:38,416
[ Cheers and applause ]
-Bravo! Amazing!

234
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:39,625
What a talent.

235
00:12:39,708 --> 00:12:41,041
I'll never accuse you

236
00:12:41,125 --> 00:12:43,583
of teaching the boring ones,
Ms. Ochiai.

237
00:12:43,666 --> 00:12:45,916
I find young talent
so volatile.

238
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,458
They burn all the brighter
when faced with one another.

239
00:12:47,541 --> 00:12:49,833
[ Chuckles ]

240
00:12:49,916 --> 00:12:52,791
Be a dear,
and thank the boy for me.

241
00:12:53,666 --> 00:12:55,750
<i>I'm right behind you, Arima.</i>

242
00:12:56,833 --> 00:12:58,083
<i>No...</i>

243
00:12:58,166 --> 00:12:59,583
<i>don't look back.</i>

244
00:12:59,666 --> 00:13:01,208
<i>Move ahead. Give it your all.</i>

245
00:13:03,208 --> 00:13:04,791
<i>You'll see me soon enough</i>

246
00:13:04,875 --> 00:13:06,458
<i>as I pass you.</i>

247
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,541
[ Cheering continues ]

248
00:13:14,541 --> 00:13:15,833
[ Gasps ]

249
00:13:20,958 --> 00:13:23,500
[ Siren wails ]

250
00:13:26,708 --> 00:13:28,125
[ Grunts ] Come on!

251
00:13:28,208 --> 00:13:30,125
All you're doing is visiting her
in the hospital!

252
00:13:30,208 --> 00:13:32,458
It's nothing
to freak out about, Kousei!

253
00:13:32,541 --> 00:13:33,875
[ Gasps ] A crow?!

254
00:13:33,958 --> 00:13:35,791
And a black cat?!

255
00:13:35,875 --> 00:13:37,458
<i>Not happening.</i>
[ Crow caws ]

256
00:13:37,541 --> 00:13:40,291
<i>Now probably wasn't</i>
<i>a good time, anyway.</i>

257
00:13:41,625 --> 00:13:43,708
<i>Somebody's a big chicken.</i>

258
00:13:44,916 --> 00:13:46,500
<i>Soon as there's some distance,</i>

259
00:13:46,583 --> 00:13:48,791
<i>it gets harder to see you,</i>

260
00:13:48,875 --> 00:13:52,458
<i>even though we spent all sorts</i>
<i>of time practicing together,</i>

261
00:13:52,541 --> 00:13:56,375
<i>I'm looking</i>
<i>for reasons to visit</i>

262
00:13:56,458 --> 00:13:58,500
<i>and reasons</i>
<i>to keep putting it off.</i>

263
00:13:58,583 --> 00:14:00,125
[ Wails ]

264
00:14:00,208 --> 00:14:02,375
[ Sputters ] Huh?

265
00:14:02,458 --> 00:14:04,708
[ Gasps ]
A freakin' water balloon!

266
00:14:04,791 --> 00:14:05,916
Konnyaku?!

267
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:07,375
And a bucket?!

268
00:14:07,458 --> 00:14:09,666
I knew today was unlucky.

269
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:11,000
[ Girl chuckles ]

270
00:14:11,083 --> 00:14:12,500
Did you like that?

271
00:14:12,583 --> 00:14:13,708
There's more
on the way.

272
00:14:13,791 --> 00:14:15,041
[ Meows ]
[ Gasps ]

273
00:14:15,125 --> 00:14:16,041
[ Screams ]

274
00:14:16,125 --> 00:14:17,541
[ Kousei groans ]

275
00:14:17,625 --> 00:14:18,875
I give up.

276
00:14:20,833 --> 00:14:22,833
Hiroko: You know
<i>mi casa es su casa,</i>

277
00:14:22,916 --> 00:14:25,333
but if you bring a girl over,
have some class.

278
00:14:25,416 --> 00:14:27,416
Don't just lug her in
like a bag of burgers.

279
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:28,416
Come on.
It's nothing like that!

280
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:30,708
Has he brought
a bag of burgers?

281
00:14:30,791 --> 00:14:32,000
I want one!

282
00:14:32,083 --> 00:14:34,125
[ Groaning ]

283
00:14:35,791 --> 00:14:37,458
She's awake.

284
00:14:37,541 --> 00:14:38,458
Thank goodness.

285
00:14:38,541 --> 00:14:40,666
[ Stammers ]

286
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:43,375
Where am I?

287
00:14:43,458 --> 00:14:45,208
You sure know
how to pick 'em, Kousei.

288
00:14:45,291 --> 00:14:46,875
Hey, kid,
you fainted out there,

289
00:14:46,958 --> 00:14:48,708
so he brought you home
like a sack of hamburgers.

290
00:14:48,791 --> 00:14:51,208
That isn't what happened!
You totally carried her in.

291
00:14:51,291 --> 00:14:53,875
Koharu: Mommy, where are
the burgers? I'm hungry!

292
00:14:53,958 --> 00:14:55,791
Pardon me for asking,

293
00:14:55,875 --> 00:14:59,541
but could you possibly be
Hiroko Seto?

294
00:14:59,625 --> 00:15:02,125
Who wants to know?

295
00:15:02,208 --> 00:15:04,416
I should introduce myself.

296
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:07,875
I'm a first year
at Kurumi-Gaoka Junior High.

297
00:15:07,958 --> 00:15:10,000
My name is Nagi Aizato.

298
00:15:10,083 --> 00:15:12,375
Their music program
is top-notch.

299
00:15:12,458 --> 00:15:13,666
You a musician?

300
00:15:13,750 --> 00:15:16,291
Yes. Yes, I am,
as a matter of fact.

301
00:15:16,375 --> 00:15:19,208
I want to be a pianist.

302
00:15:19,291 --> 00:15:23,250
<i>What's an aspiring pianist</i>
<i>doing up in a tree?</i>

303
00:15:23,333 --> 00:15:25,875
Honestly, I'm one
of your biggest fans, Ms. Seto,

304
00:15:25,958 --> 00:15:27,000
so please take me on
as a student!

305
00:15:27,083 --> 00:15:30,250
-Huh?
-I beg of you!

306
00:15:30,333 --> 00:15:34,041
Uh, I don't usually go
for the hard sell, kiddo.

307
00:15:34,125 --> 00:15:35,666
Plus it's kind of
a slap in the face

308
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:38,625
to your current teacher, right?
Tell you what.

309
00:15:38,708 --> 00:15:41,125
If this is something
you really want to pursue,

310
00:15:41,208 --> 00:15:42,791
go show me what you got.

311
00:15:44,291 --> 00:15:45,375
Alright, then.

312
00:15:49,541 --> 00:15:51,666
Your posture's good,
so that's a plus.

313
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:55,000
What are you going to play?
Maybe a little Bach?

314
00:15:55,083 --> 00:15:58,583
No, Chopin's
"Etude Opus 25, Number 5."

315
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:00,583
[ Gasps ]
<i>That was Kousei's piece</i>

316
00:16:00,666 --> 00:16:01,958
<i>at the Maihou Competition.</i>

317
00:16:02,041 --> 00:16:04,291
[ Breathes deeply ]

318
00:16:04,375 --> 00:16:06,333
[ Playing
"Etude Opus 25, Number 5" ]

319
00:16:06,416 --> 00:16:10,791
♪♪

320
00:16:10,875 --> 00:16:13,958
[ Gasps ]

321
00:16:17,958 --> 00:16:20,458
<i>She's good.</i>

322
00:16:20,541 --> 00:16:22,625
♪♪

323
00:16:22,708 --> 00:16:24,125
<i>The notes are all there,</i>

324
00:16:24,208 --> 00:16:26,791
<i>but why does it</i>
<i>sound so harsh?</i>

325
00:16:26,875 --> 00:16:30,041
♪♪

326
00:16:30,125 --> 00:16:34,000
<i>A song like this.</i>

327
00:16:34,083 --> 00:16:35,791
<i>A song like this.</i>

328
00:16:35,875 --> 00:16:44,791
♪♪

329
00:16:44,875 --> 00:16:46,708
That was really pretty!

330
00:16:46,791 --> 00:16:48,875
Your music program
is no slouch.

331
00:16:48,958 --> 00:16:51,833
Are all the first years
playing like that nowadays?

332
00:16:51,916 --> 00:16:54,500
Wow,
and after fainting, no less.

333
00:16:54,583 --> 00:16:57,291
Was that,
you know, good enough?

334
00:16:58,666 --> 00:17:00,208
Hmm.

335
00:17:01,083 --> 00:17:03,000
Alright.
[ Gasps ]

336
00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:06,458
[ Crying ]

337
00:17:06,541 --> 00:17:07,833
Thank you so much!

338
00:17:07,916 --> 00:17:09,041
You don't
got to cry about it.

339
00:17:09,125 --> 00:17:11,833
I can't believe
I'm gonna get piano lessons

340
00:17:11,916 --> 00:17:13,958
from<i> the</i> Hiroko Seto!

341
00:17:14,041 --> 00:17:15,583
<i>Mission accomplished.</i>

342
00:17:15,666 --> 00:17:16,333
She's so happy.

343
00:17:16,416 --> 00:17:18,666
Hey, Kousei.
Uh-huh.

344
00:17:18,750 --> 00:17:19,833
You don't mind
teaching her, right?

345
00:17:19,916 --> 00:17:21,666
[ Gulps ]

346
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:23,791
Huh?!

347
00:17:23,875 --> 00:17:25,750
[ Meows ]

348
00:17:27,875 --> 00:17:29,083
Clerk: Thank you very much.

349
00:17:29,166 --> 00:17:30,708
[ Entry bell chimes ]

350
00:17:33,791 --> 00:17:37,625
<i>Alright, no black cats</i>
<i>or crows this time.</i>

351
00:17:37,708 --> 00:17:39,083
<i>Plus I got her a gift.</i>

352
00:17:39,166 --> 00:17:41,041
<i>If I don't see her,</i>

353
00:17:41,125 --> 00:17:41,875
<i>they'll just go stale.</i>

354
00:17:41,958 --> 00:17:44,375
<i>Yeah.</i>

355
00:17:44,458 --> 00:17:46,666
<i>Of course I'd drop by</i>
<i>for a visit.</i>

356
00:17:46,750 --> 00:17:48,625
<i>I'm her accompanist.</i>
<i>That's what you do.</i>

357
00:17:53,291 --> 00:17:57,625
<i>Coming or going, I'm always</i>
<i>looking for a good excuse.</i>

358
00:18:00,625 --> 00:18:03,125
Watari: So he's totally soaked
from head to toe, right.

359
00:18:03,208 --> 00:18:04,375
[ Kaori laughs ]
Nakamura starts laughing

360
00:18:04,458 --> 00:18:07,416
so hard that snot
just rockets out of his nose.

361
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:09,375
Gross!
So I start busting up, too,

362
00:18:09,458 --> 00:18:11,750
and, boom, more snot!
[ Both laugh ]

363
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:13,916
<i>Canelés?</i>

364
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:16,125
<i>Her parents own a bakery.</i>

365
00:18:16,208 --> 00:18:19,416
<i>It's a good thing</i>
<i>I didn't actually go in.</i>

366
00:18:22,291 --> 00:18:24,250
<i>I'm such an idiot.</i>

367
00:18:24,333 --> 00:18:25,916
[ Cat meowing ]

368
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:33,250
♪♪

369
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:35,333
[ Cellphone rings ]
[ Yelps ]

370
00:18:37,375 --> 00:18:39,583
No name?

371
00:18:39,666 --> 00:18:41,833
Kaori: You're a big old jerk!
You know that?!

372
00:18:41,916 --> 00:18:43,583
Watari always
comes to visit me!

373
00:18:43,666 --> 00:18:45,625
But Friend A
just can't be bothered.

374
00:18:45,708 --> 00:18:47,375
What a butt-head!
Huh?

375
00:18:47,458 --> 00:18:49,875
Wait a sec.
How did you even get my number?

376
00:18:49,958 --> 00:18:51,916
I realized I hadn't
heard your dumb voice

377
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,625
for a while, so --

378
00:18:53,708 --> 00:18:55,958
You were eating
something sweet, weren't you?

379
00:18:56,041 --> 00:18:58,625
Yeah, a canelé.

380
00:18:58,708 --> 00:19:00,958
Lucky! I wish
I could have a canelé.

381
00:19:01,041 --> 00:19:02,166
[ Sighs ]

382
00:19:03,916 --> 00:19:05,708
How about
I bring you some?

383
00:19:05,791 --> 00:19:08,583
No kidding?
You promise you'll do it?

384
00:19:08,666 --> 00:19:09,541
Yeah.

385
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:13,458
<i>You remind me of a cat.</i>

386
00:19:13,541 --> 00:19:15,000
<i>When I reach out to you,</i>

387
00:19:15,083 --> 00:19:18,291
<i>you turn tail</i>
<i>and run off in a huff.</i>

388
00:19:18,375 --> 00:19:20,625
<i>But when you're hurt,</i>
<i>you get playful,</i>

389
00:19:20,708 --> 00:19:22,125
<i>like you haven't</i>
<i>a care in the world.</i>

390
00:19:22,208 --> 00:19:24,708
<i>You're contrary,</i>

391
00:19:24,791 --> 00:19:26,791
<i>and I love that about you.</i>

392
00:19:26,875 --> 00:19:30,750
Actually, can you grab me
my Dad's canelés?

393
00:19:30,833 --> 00:19:33,166
[ Grunts ]
Cross your heart?

394
00:19:33,250 --> 00:19:34,833
Mm-hmm.

395
00:19:34,916 --> 00:19:38,333
<i>I don't know why,</i>
<i>but canelés at night,</i>

396
00:19:38,416 --> 00:19:40,083
<i>they taste better somehow.</i>

397
00:19:40,166 --> 00:19:42,291
Yeah. [ Sighs ]

398
00:19:42,375 --> 00:19:43,875
Totally called it.

399
00:19:43,958 --> 00:19:48,000
I knew her face looked familiar
from somewhere.

400
00:19:48,083 --> 00:19:49,583
Hmm.

401
00:19:51,041 --> 00:19:52,875
♪<i> Nous, nous canelé</i> ♪

402
00:19:52,958 --> 00:19:54,166
♪<i> Canelé pour nous</i> ♪

403
00:19:54,250 --> 00:19:56,291
Ohh! [ Grunts ]

404
00:19:56,375 --> 00:19:57,583
[ Sighs ]

405
00:19:58,208 --> 00:20:00,000
I fell.

406
00:20:00,083 --> 00:20:03,791
[ Panting ]

407
00:20:03,875 --> 00:20:04,333
What the...

408
00:20:04,416 --> 00:20:06,791
[ Gasping ]

409
00:20:21,083 --> 00:20:22,916
[ Gasps ]

410
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,166
[ Grunting ]

411
00:20:24,250 --> 00:20:26,083
[ Sliding ]

412
00:20:26,166 --> 00:20:28,083
[ Grunting, groaning ]

413
00:20:42,208 --> 00:20:45,041
[ Panting ]

414
00:20:48,083 --> 00:20:50,208
[ Gasping ]

415
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,083
[ Yells ]

416
00:20:57,791 --> 00:21:00,416
Stupid legs! Stand up!

417
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:01,416
You're supposed to do
what I say,

418
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:03,500
so stand up, already!

419
00:21:03,583 --> 00:21:06,125
What are you waiting for?!
Stand up!

420
00:21:07,666 --> 00:21:09,333
[ Crying ]

421
00:21:15,291 --> 00:21:18,833
[ Screams ]

422
00:21:20,208 --> 00:21:22,083
[ "Orange" playing ]
[ Singing in Japanese ]

423
00:21:22,166 --> 00:21:31,916
♪♪

424
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:41,583
♪♪

425
00:21:41,666 --> 00:21:51,208
♪♪

426
00:21:51,291 --> 00:22:00,125
♪♪

427
00:22:00,208 --> 00:22:10,666
♪♪

428
00:22:10,750 --> 00:22:20,333
♪♪

429
00:22:20,416 --> 00:22:29,208
♪♪

430
00:22:29,291 --> 00:22:39,833
♪♪

431
